HomeTrust Bancshares, Inc. Key Developments

HomeTrust Bancshares, Inc. Announces Audited Earnings Results for the Fourth Quarter and Full Year Ended June 30, 2017
Jul 26 17
HomeTrust Bancshares, Inc. announced audited earnings results for the fourth quarter and full year ended June 30, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported net interest income of $24,567,000 against $20,766,000 a year ago. Income before income taxes was $6,966,000 against $4,708,000 a year ago. Net income was $4,766,000 or $0.25 diluted per share against $3,302,000 or $0.19 basic and diluted per share a year ago. Return on assets was 0.61% against 0.48% a year ago. Return on assets – adjusted was 0.61% against 0.52% a year ago. Return on equity was 4.83% against 3.68% a year ago. Return on equity – adjusted was 4.88% against 3.96% a year ago. Net income (non-GAAP) was $4,809,000 or $0.25 diluted per share against $3,548,000 or $0.21 basic and diluted per share a year ago. The leading factors in the increase of net income was an increase in net interest income from organic loan growth and the acquisition of TriSummit Bancorp, Inc. and its wholly-owned subsidiary TriSummit Bank, which outpaced all merger-related expenses. Net interest income increased as compared to the same period a year ago, primarily due to a $4.9 million increase in interest income driven by an increase in average-interest earning assets.

For the year, the company reported net interest income of $91,191,000 against $81,707,000 a year ago. Income before income taxes was $17,039,000 against $16,357,000 a year ago. Net income was $11,847,000 or $0.65 diluted per share against $11,456,000 or $0.65 basic and diluted per share a year ago. Return on assets was 0.40% against 0.42% a year ago. Return on assets – adjusted was 0.58% against 0.45% a year ago. Return on equity was 3.14% against 3.16% a year ago. Return on equity – adjusted was 4.54% against 3.37% a year ago. Book value per share as on June 30, 2017 was $20.96 against $20.00 as at June 30, 2016. Tangible book value per share as on June 30, 2017 was $19.37 against $19.05 as at June 30, 2016. Net income (non-GAAP) was $17,111,000 or $0.94 diluted per share against $12,228,000 or $0.70 basic and diluted per share a year ago. The leading factors in the increase of net income was an increase in net interest income from organic loan growth and the acquisition of TriSummit Bancorp, Inc. and its wholly-owned subsidiary TriSummit Bank, which outpaced all merger-related expenses.


HomeTrust Bancshares, Inc. Announces Unaudited Earnings Results for the Third Quarter and Nine Months Ended March 31, 2017
Apr 27 17
HomeTrust Bancshares, Inc. announced unaudited earnings results for the third quarter and nine months ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported net interest income of $25,072,000 compared to $20,220,000 a year ago. Loss before income taxes was $51,000 compared to profit of $4,231,000 a year ago. Net income was $274,000 or $0.01 per basic and diluted share compared to $3,141,000 or $0.18 per basic and diluted share a year ago. Return on assets (ratio of net income to average total assets) was 0.04% compared to 0.46% a year ago. Return on assets - adjusted was 0.64% compared to 0.46% a year ago. Return on equity (ratio of net income to average equity) was 3.49% compared to 1.22% a year ago. Return on equity – adjusted was 5.20% compared to 3.49% a year ago. As at March 31, 2017, the company’s book value per share was $20.62 compared to $19.72 a year ago. As at March 31, 2017, the company’s tangible book value per share was $19.01 compared to $18.76 a year ago. Net income (non-GAAP) was $5,005,000 or $0.27 per basic and diluted share compared to $3,131,000 or $0.18 per basic and diluted share a year ago. Return on equity (ratio of net income to average equity) was 0.28% compared to 3.49% a year ago.

For the nine months, the company reported net interest income of $66,624,000 compared to $60,941,000 a year ago. Income before income taxes was $10,073,000 compared to $11,649,000 a year ago. Net income was $7,081,000 or $0.40 per basic and diluted share compared to $8,154,000 or $0.46 per basic and diluted share a year ago. Return on assets (ratio of net income to average total assets) was 0.33% compared to 0.40% a year ago. Return on assets - adjusted was 0.57% compared to 0.42% a year ago. Return on equity (ratio of net income to average equity) was 2.54% compared to 2.98% a year ago. Return on equity – adjusted was 4.42% compared to 3.18% a year ago. As at March 31, 2017, the company’s book value per share was $20.62 compared to $19.72 a year ago. As at March 31, 2017, the company’s tangible book value per share was $19.01 compared to $18.76 a year ago. Net income (non-GAAP) was $12,301,000 or $0.69 per basic and diluted share compared to $8,674,000 or $0.49 per diluted share a year ago.


HomeTrust Bancshares, Inc. Reports Earnings Results for the Second Quarter and Six Months Ended December 31, 2016
Jan 26 17
HomeTrust Bancshares, Inc. reported earnings results for the second quarter and six months ended December 31, 2016. For the quarter, the company reported total interest income of $22.063 million compared to $21.566 million a year ago. Net interest income was $20.415 million compared to $20.150 million a year ago. Income before income taxes was $3.876 million compared to $3.313 million a year ago. Net income was $2.983 million or $0.17 per diluted share compared to $2.449 million or $0.14 per diluted share a year ago. Return on assets was 0.43% compared to 0.36% a year ago. Return on equity was 3.26% compared to 2.7% a year ago. Return on assets – adjusted was 0.43% compared to 0.36% a year ago. Return on equity – adjusted was 3.28% compared to 2.70% a year ago. Book value per share as at December 31, 2016 was $20.43 compared to $19.44 a year ago. Tangible book value per share as at December 31, 2016 was $19.50 compared to $18.47 a year ago. Non-GAAP net income was $3.000 million compared to $2.449 million a year ago. Adjusted net income per diluted share was $0.17 compared to $0.14 a year ago. 

For six months, the company reported total interest income of $44.854 million compared to $43.575 million a year ago. Net interest income was $41.552 million compared to $40.721 million a year ago. Income before income taxes was $10.124 million compared to $7.418 million a year ago. Net income was $6.807 million or $0.39 per diluted share compared to $5.013 million or $0.28 per diluted share a year ago. Return on assets was 0.49% compared to 0.36% a year ago. Return on equity was 3.74% compared to 2.73% a year ago. Return on assets – adjusted was 0.53% compared to 0.40% a year ago. Return on equity – adjusted was 4.01% compared to 3.02% a year ago. Non-GAAP net income was $7.295 million compared to $5.539 million a year ago. Adjusted net income per diluted share was $0.42 compared to $0.31 a year ago.


